<zk>
	<label multiline="true">
		ZK-4305 Footer — popup shows Clear and Cancel buttons

		Steps to verify:
		1. Click the calendar button — the popup opens showing a footer bar at the bottom.
		2. The footer contains two small buttons: Clear (left) and Cancel (right).
		3. Click a day to stage begin. Then click Clear — staging is discarded.
		4. Select a complete range. Then click Clear — inputs revert to empty.
		5. Stage a begin date. Then click Cancel — popup closes, inputs stay empty.

		Expected result:
		- Footer always rendered with Clear and Cancel buttons.
		- Clear resets both staged and committed values.
		- Cancel closes the popup without committing any staged selection.
		- Each panel only shows its own month — no faded next/previous-month dates.
	</label>

	<vlayout spacing="10px" hflex="1">
		<label value="Basic footer box:"/>
		<daterangebox id="drFooter" format="yyyy-MM-dd" width="360px"/>

		<label value="Footer with pre-committed range (to test Clear erases committed value):"/>
		<daterangebox id="drPreset" format="yyyy-MM-dd" width="360px"/>
		<zscript><![CDATA[
			import java.util.Calendar;
			Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();
			cal.set(2026, Calendar.JANUARY, 5, 0, 0, 0);
			cal.set(Calendar.MILLISECOND, 0);
			java.util.Date begin = cal.getTime();
			cal.set(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH, 20);
			java.util.Date end = cal.getTime();
			drPreset.setBeginValue(begin);
			drPreset.setEndValue(end);
		]]></zscript>
	</vlayout>
</zk>
